proot: proot (chroot, mount --bind, and binfmt_misc without any privilege)
proot:
proot: PRoot is a rewrite of chroot, mount --bind, and binfmt_misc in
proot: user-mode, so that you do not need any privilege to -respectively-
proot: use an arbitrary directory as a root file-system, make files
proot: accessible somewhere else in the file-system hierarchy, and execute
proot: programs built for another CPU architecture transparently with
proot: the help of a CPU emulator like QEMU. PRoot relies on ptrace, an
proot: unprivileged system-call available in every Linux kernels and also
proot: used by User-Mode Linux, strace, and GDB.
proot: Home: http://proot.me
